d fictional works, The Victorian aquarium unearths the historical significance of nineteenth-century tanks, reconstructing their far-ranging cultural resonance.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aAquariumsxSocial aspectszGreat BritainxHistoryy19th century. 0aInterior decorationzGreat BritainxHistoryy19th century. 4aLiterature Studies 2021. 7aHISTORY / Europe / Great Britain / Victorian Era (1837-1901).2bisacsh  aVictorian aquarium.  aanimal studies.  acollecting.  aecocriticism.  aliterature and science.  amaterial culture.  anatural history.  apopular science.  aseaside tourism.  asubmarine environment.1 aGranata, Silvia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2021 eBook-Packagez978311128198840uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152615197140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526151971423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526151971/original  a978-3-11-128198-8  Manchester University Press 2021 eBook-Packageb2021  aGBV-deGruyter-alles